DataElement.preferredDefinition: Process of using a rotating machine to generate centrifugal force to separate substances of different densities, remove moisture, or simulate gravitational effects. It employs a large motor-driven apparatus with a long arm, at the end of which human and animal subjects, biological specimens, or equipment can be revolved and rotated at various speeds to study gravitational effects. (From Websters, 10th ed; McGraw-Hill Dictionary of Scientific and Technical Terms, 4th ed):Something that happens at a given place and time.:Any factor that defines a system and determines (or limits) its performance._A unit measure of time equal to 60 seconds.:The period of time during which something continues._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is an Integer (32-bit two's complement).

Concepts.definition: A process where a rotating machine exposes a specimen to centrifugal force. This process can be used to remove moisture from a specimen, to subject an organism to increased gravitational forces, or to separate the components of heterogeneous mixtures based on density differences.
